review_blob: Bottle: 500ml. Aroma: Hoppy, pine and resin. Alcoholic, grainy and malty. A bit hazy in apperance, ok head. Taste: Bitter and sweet, too bitter. Not a nice balance in taste. Soapy in palate. A beer with a lack of balance.
Aroma: Sulfury, woody, cheese, diacetylic. Taste: Diacetylic, a bit hoppy. Nice bitterness and well balanced in taste. Medium bodied, a bit harsch. A nice lager.
Bottle 250ml. Aroma: Benzaldehyde, fruity. Taste: Too sweet, a bit sour, low bitterness. Overall modified kriek. Artificial.

Bottle 330ml. Aroma: Malty, nice brettyness, hoppy, smoke, citrus, cloves, sour, fruity. Hazy, pale, appearance with a thick nice head. Taste: Sharp and nice bitterness, a bit tart, grape fruity, dry. High carbonation. Overall a beer with a very nice and complex aroma. Different and pleasant.
Aroma: Stable, gun powder, fruit, cheese (parmesan). Nice head, hazy. Sour taste, taste like grape fruit (sour and bitter). A bit harsh palate. An interesting product but could be more balanced.
Bottle. Aroma: cocoa, coffee, alcohol, hoppy, burnt and toasted. Nice head nd appearance. Dry and tart taste. Fizzy and harsh palate. Could be more balanced
Bottle. Caramel, Apple juice, yeast, stable, mushroom in aroma. Taste: sweet Apple juice, sourish and mushrooms. Ok cider

Bottle. Fruity, citrusy, piney, malty, raisiny, alcoholic and Madeira aroma. Nice appearance, amber. High bitterness,  bit too sharp.  Little unbalanced in taste. Medium-full body and harsh in palate. Overall  nice ipa with very pleasant aroma.
Bottle 330ml. Aroma: pine, hoppy, oxidised, sulphury, sweaty feet. Clear nice appearance. Sharp bitterness, watery. No balanced beer.
Bottle as Vrwit. Aroma: Fenolic, smoke, sweet, vegetables. Unbalanced taste, umami. Nice appearance. A bit too dark? High Co2, light bodied. Not a great wit.

Bottle 330 ml. Aroma: cooked vegetables, corn, grassy and spicy hops, sweet grainy aroma. Pale yellow and clear appearance with average lasting head. Taste: Sharp nice bitterness and nice balanced. Overall a nice german pilsener. C
Bottle 330ml. Aroma: Bretty, leather, barnyard, fruity, toasted, roasted, smoke. Dark brown color. Taste: A bit sour, nice bitterness. Thin body. Overall a very nice flavorful beer.

Bottle 330ml. Fruity, estery, spicy, perfume like aroma. Nicely hazy, nice bubbling from CO2, the head is quite quickly diminishing. Very good balance in taste, nice bitterness. Very nice and oily palate. Overall a very nice beer.
Aroma: caramel, strawberry, raisins, roasted. A bit unbalanced in taste. Too light. Hazy appearance with light head. Palate is light and harsch with fizzy carbonation. Overall too light.
Aroma: brett, spices, diacetyl, alcohol, iron, vegetables. Sweet in taste with high bitterness. Clear in appearance with ok head. Fizzy carbonation. A bit too unbalanced.
Aroma: citrus hops, nice aroma, caramel, toffee, some vegetables, alcohol. Well balanced in taste. Very cloudy with ok head. Harsch palate. Too much quality problems.
Aroma: caramel, iron, blood. Sweet, nasty taste. Nice reddish color with minimal head. Not drinkable. Like putting iron nails and sugar in your mouth. Probably large problems with this badge.
Aroma: yeast, alcohol. Unbalanced taste. Sweet, bitter, strong. Bad head. Not at all as hoppy as you think. Hop-it?
Aroma: smoke, alcohol, rust, sweet, licorice. Nice taste with well balanced bitterness. A bit harsch but creamy still. Ok head, a bit shady. Overall a nice beer.
Brett and slightly oxidized aroma. Lactic acidic taste. Nice clear color with ok head. Harsch palate and too light bodied. Not a very nice porter.
Aroma: honey, brett, vegetables. Very sweet taste. Hazy appearance with bad head. Lively carbonation. Overall too sweet!
Aroma is fruity, hoppy, honey, sweet. Nice taste but dont last as long as you want. Ok head, nice light amber. Harsch palate and too light bodied. Not that well balanced in taste.
Aroma: fruity, strawberry, tree. Taste is well balanced with medium but long bitterness. Nice appearance with ok head. Lively palate. Overall a good and interesting christmas beer.

Aroma: lactic adid, vinagre, brett, rotten. The taste is way too sweet, and a lot of iron. Very nice appearance with a clear color. Ok head. Full bodied with lively carbonation. Not our type of beer at all.
UPDATED: FEB 20, 2011

Bottle 330 ml. golden, clear appearance with a lasting thin head. Aroma: Sweet, hoppy, diacetyl, unfortunately quite oxidised. Sweet (sweeter than I remember) taste with a distinct bitterness. Light body with average carbonation, a bit oily in palate. The beer was very oxidised which lowers the aroma and overall score. I dont  think thats acceptable when it is 5 months left of the shelf life. The high sweetness lowers the taste and overall score for me as well . I must say that Im dissapointed of the beer in the bottle I drunk. I will try it again some time to see if it was a coincidence. C
Bottle 330ml at Idala grd. Aroma: sweet, grainy, corn, vegetables. Sweet taste with low bitterness, nice clear appearance, diminishing head. C
Bottle 330 ml. Aroma: Banana, sweet, phenolic, estery, fruity, alcohol. Taste: sweet, a bit umami, the bitterness is not balanced with the sweetness. No balanced beer.
Can 330 ml. Aroma: metallic, corn, grainy, cardboard,  bit grassy hops. sharp german bitterness, quite nice taste. Some harshness in palate.  An ok pilsner.
Can 330 ml. Aroma: cooked vegetables, plain. Sweet in taste. Ok bitterness. Minimal head.
Bottle 500ml. Aroma: sulfury, hops, malt. Taste: sour, medium bitterness. Not too balanced. Light bodied and soft carbonation. Clear amber with light head. /A
Bottle 500ml. Aroma: chocolate, raisins, vanilla, toasted. To sweet for me. Oxidised and tart in taste.
Bottle 330ml. Aroma: metallic, cardboard, sweet, corn. Taste: medium bitterness, ok balance in taste.  bit harsh. Medium body. Ok appearance. Ok beer with some quality faults.
Can 330ml. Minimal head, clear light yellow appearance. Fruity, a bit grainy, cooked vegetables, corn, metallic aroma. Almost no bitterness, watery in taste and palate. A very plain beer. C
Bottle 330 in the Seal. Aroma: Fruity, plain. Taste: tart, no perfect balance between sweetness and bitterness. Harsh in palate, high carbonation, thin body but sweet. A not to perfect brew.

Can 500ml in the Seal. Aroma: A bit grainy, diacetylic , sweet and metallic. Otherwise very plain in aroma. Clean and plain taste, a bit umami, low bitterness. No lasting head. Oily and creamy in palate, thin body, average carbonation, A very plain beer but no off flavours.
Bottle 500 ml. Aroma: nice smoke aroma, toasted. A bit tart in taste. Lively cabonated. Harsh and quite light body. A quite nice brew.
Can 330 ml. rotten eggs, grainy and plain aroma. Watery in taste and light body. very plain beer.
Can 330ml. Aroma: Cooked vegetables, grainy. Taste: Sweet, low bitterness. Harsh and light bodied palate. Diminishing head. No great beer.
355ml bottle. Aroma: chocolate, coffee, caramel, licorice, alcohol. Sweet and bitter taste. A bit roasted. Medium bodied with average carbonation. Overall too sweet, but enjoyable.

Aroma: Yeasty, caramel, spicy, alcohol, portwine like, figs. Appearance: Nice amber color, moderate head. Taste: Sweet, umami. Palate: Full bodied. 
To sweet for us. Not our kind of beer.
Coffee, toasted malt, liqorice, grainy, fruity aroma. A bit tart, not fully balanced taste. Harsh in palate. A nice stout with some unbalance in taste and too harsh.
UPDATED: FEB 20, 2011
Hoppy, alcoholic, a bit sulphury, ashey aroma. Pale, clear and ok head. Harsh and quite thin palate. Sweet and bitter taste not totally in balance. overall an ok and nice beer.
Pale, ok head, a bit dirt in the beer. Grain, citrus, resin, funky, hoppy aroma. Distinct bitterness. Thin palate. Interesting beer but not a classic pilsner.
Aroma: American citrus hops, sweet, spicy, alcohol. Large head and hazy appearance. Sweet taste. Nice beer except theres too much carbon dioxide.
Aroma is yeasty, spicy, alcohol. Nice yellow appearance, like apple juice. Well balanced and smooth taste. Fizzy and a bit harsh palate. A nice tripel!
Aroma: wood, smoke, caramel, a bit cooked vegetables. Hazy, reddish appearance with bad head. Taste is sweet and quite sour. Sparkling palate. Interesting beer, too sweet though.
UPDATED: FEB 4, 2011
Sweet and fresh aroma, malty, hoppy, caramel. Nice head. Well balanced taste. A bit harsh palate. Interesting beer, but theres something missing.
